          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:anchor>289</fr:anchor>
            <fr:addr type="user">FA-0079</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>FA-0079.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Orthonormal Basis">Orthonormal Basis</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
              <fr:month>5</fr:month>
              <fr:day>26</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>Long Nguyen</fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>A complete (in the sense of <fr:link type="local" href="FA-0072.xml" addr="FA-0072" title="Completeness of orthonormal set">Completeness of orthonormal set</fr:link>) <fr:link type="local" href="FA-0073.xml" addr="FA-0073" title="Orthonormal">orthonormal</fr:link> subset (<fr:link type="local" href="FA-0029.xml" addr="FA-0029" title="Orthonormal sequence">orthonormal sequence</fr:link>) of H is also called an <fr:link type="local" href="FA-0073.xml" addr="FA-0073" title="Orthonormal">orthonormal</fr:link> <fr:link type="local" href="FA-0074.xml" addr="FA-0074" title="Basis">basis</fr:link> of H</fr:p>
            <fr:p><fr:strong>Altenately</fr:strong>: An <fr:link type="local" href="FA-0073.xml" addr="FA-0073" title="Orthonormal">orthonormal</fr:link> <fr:link type="local" href="FA-0074.xml" addr="FA-0074" title="Basis">basis</fr:link> of H is a <fr:link type="local" href="FA-0075.xml" addr="FA-0075" title="Countable">countable</fr:link> <fr:link type="local" href="FA-0076.xml" addr="FA-0076" title="Maximal orthonormal set">maximal</fr:link> <fr:link type="local" href="FA-0073.xml" addr="FA-0073" title="Orthonormal">orthonormal</fr:link> subset <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\{e_n\}]]></fr:tex> of H.</fr:p>
            <fr:p><fr:strong>N.B.</fr:strong>: This notion of <fr:link type="local" href="FA-0074.xml" addr="FA-0074" title="Basis">basis</fr:link> is <fr:em>not quite the same</fr:em> as in the <fr:em>finite dimensional case</fr:em> (although it is a legitimate extension of it).</fr:p>
            <fr:p>There are other, quite different, notions of a <fr:link type="local" href="FA-0074.xml" addr="FA-0074" title="Basis">basis</fr:link> in <fr:link type="local" href="FA-0005.xml" addr="FA-0005" title="Infinite Dimensions">infinite dimensions</fr:link>. See for instance '<fr:link type="local" href="FA-0077.xml" addr="FA-0077" title="Hamel basis">Hamel basis</fr:link>' which arises in some settings</fr:p>
            <fr:p>
              <fr:strong>Theorem:</fr:strong>
            </fr:p>
            <fr:p>Every <fr:link type="local" href="FA-0078.xml" addr="FA-0078" title="Separable space">separable</fr:link> <fr:link type="local" href="FA-0030.xml" addr="FA-0030" title="Hilbert Space">Hilbert space</fr:link> has a <fr:link type="local" href="FA-0075.xml" addr="FA-0075" title="Countable">countable</fr:link> orthonormal <fr:link type="local" href="FA-0074.xml" addr="FA-0074" title="Basis">basis</fr:link>.</fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
          <fr:backmatter />
        </fr:tree>
      </fr:mainmatter>
      <fr:backmatter />
    </fr:tree>
